		<htmltext><![CDATA[
			<p><b>Temperature</b></p>
			<p>Design of modules shall be such that abnormal temperature-rise conditions are prevented . If the temperature of the hottest cell exceeds the maximum safe charging temperature, charging shall be terminated.  Localized heating might come from a cell fault, from external heating by the system, or by the end user placing the equipment close to a heat source.</p>
			<p>Over-temperature protection shall be incorporated to prevent operation outside temperature limits. Temperature ranges shall be based on ambient temperature as well as the effects of heat interactions.   The battery pack shall contain at least one thermal protection circuit or device independent of internal cell devices or mechanisms. The combination of cell, module, and host device/charger shall have at least two independent thermal protection devices or mechanisms.  In case of an exceeding of the temperature limit, actions shaal be taken. This can include shutdown or other protective action.</p>
		]]></htmltext>
