		<htmltext><![CDATA[
			<p><b>Charging</b></p>
			<p>Batteries shall be provided with specifications and charging instructions from equipment manufacturers so that associated chargers are designed to maintain charging within the temperature, voltage and current limits specified.  Before charge, the control system shall determine if the module is within the condition for operation specified by the manufacturer. Charging shall be conducted in accordance with the conditions specified of the cell specification sheet.  The charge control may be located in the battery module.  The charge voltage of each cell block shall be monitored and controlled. If a block cell block reaches the specified maximum charge, the charging of the cell blocks shall be ceased. If the cell voltage rises beyond the maximum charge voltage to the cell critical voltage, the pack shall be permanently disabled for charging . In addition to the voltage limit designed into the charging circuit, the battery management circuit shall incorporate at least two independent overvoltage protection functions. At least one of these protection functions shall be in the pack.</p>
		]]></htmltext>
