		<htmltext><![CDATA[
			<p><b>Discharging</b></p>
			<p>To control the discharge, the minimum discharge voltage and the maximum discharge current shall be set on the basis of a cell specification sheet. The module shall have at least one overcurrent protect circuitry or device . A system analysis shall define the maximum current that the system can handle. The module shall have at least one undervoltage protection circuit. If any cell block is detected with a voltage equal or less than specified by the cell manufacturer, the module shall cease to provide power. If one or more cell blocks reaches the minimum operating voltage, the management circuit shall maintain a low-power stat in order to minimize further discharge of the cells.
			If a cell or cell block is discharge beyond the expected minimum state, the cell manufacturer’s recommendation to recover from this condition shall be followed.  A nascent short in a cell can be detected by measuring excessive self discharge of cells or the ac impedance of cells.  If an unusual voltage behavior of one cell block versus another is measured, an open circuit cells is detected</p>
		]]></htmltext>
