			<p><b>Communication</b></p>
			<p>For portable application, data can be communicated between the module and the device in which it is used. The module shall give info about the condition of the pack, about potential battery issues as they occur. In cases where a hazard may result, the battery shall fail-safe. If the device does not respond within a dined time period to a message indicating a potential hazard, the battery shall take action. An alternative signal or fail-safe method should be provided in the event of a failure of the primary signaling method. 
			The management circuit should store key behavioral data. Information should be maintained for at least three charge terminations with the reason for termination. The data should be stored in non-volatile memory.</p>
